items.name: Disney Renaissance Style (LORA)
items.description:
I based this model off of the classic art style from movies of the Disney Renaissance (The Little Mermaid, Aladdin, Beauty and the Beast, The Lion King, etc) from 1989 all the way up to 1999. The art style composes of thin outlines, detailed characters and objects, shades and dimensions of colors, and painted backgrounds.

(v2.0 UPDATE): Fixed the model to become more accurate with locations and people. It's better for you to start off a prompt with this: disney style (insert subject here), your details

Recommended settings:

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras, DPM++ SDE Karras, or Euler a (three of the best samplers, imo)

LoRA weight: ~0.8-1

CFG scale: ~5.5-7

If you are doing hires. fix, I recommend the denoising weight of ~0.55-0.7, since if you go further, the model tends to become more realistic and not as cartoony.

When it comes to locations, use the bracket signs ( ) to add weight to your prompt, just so you can have a better chance for getting the locations to you want.

Make sure to add the trigger word "disney style" to activate it.

It's optional, but just in case, if your images result in a realistic photo, just add the words:

cartoon, disney style

Checkpoints: I recommend Deliberate since that was the only model that was able to match the Disney art style more accurately, but you can try different styles to your liking.

Negative prompt that works well:

deformed, bad anatomy, disfigured, poorly drawn face, mutation, mutated, extra limb, ugly, disgusting, poorly drawn hands, missing limb, floating limbs, disconnected limbs, malformed hands, blurry, ((mutated hands and fingers)), duplicate images, duplicate, (deformed, distorted, disfigured:1.3), poorly drawn, bad anatomy, wrong anatomy, extra limb, missing limb, floating limbs, (mutated hands and fingers:1.4), disconnected limbs, mutation, mutated, ugly, disgusting, blurry, amputation, EasyNegative, ng_deepnegative_v1_75t

DeepNegative and EasyNegative are very recommended.

This is only the first version, and I will iron out any problems in the next ones.

Suggestions and feedback are welcome! I hope you enjoy!

items.name: Thundarr the Barbarian - Thundarr
items.description:
LORDS OF LIGHT!

I noticed a distinct lack of 80's characters on here and being a Gen-X'er, I had to rectify that issue. To continue the series, I now present the next in a series of heroes - Thundarr from Thundarr the Barbarian. This Lora was trained on images from the 1980's cartoon.

Image was trained on SD1.5, so it is good for most other checkpoints. I would recommend setting the strength to 0.5-0.7. Highres.fx = VERY YES. I usually go about 1/2 of my initial steps with a denoising strength of 0.3-0.4.

Activation word is "thundarr". The AI has no idea what a "sunsword" is, so you'll want to use "yellow lightsaber" or "energy sword". Also, you may have to put "beard" into your negatives because it keeps wanting to give Thundarr a goatee. You figure that one out. Good luck, have fun, and stay tuned for more 80's icons!

items.description:
Note#1: I trriiiiiiieeeeed to get her iconic eyes but I'm missing something at getting it to work consistently. I might try again later but I didn't feel like rebuilding it yet again to try to get it to work after multiple tries :(.

What does it do you ask? While not as cool as the main characters in Miss Kobayashi's Dragon Maid, Lucoa brings in some hefty proportions to the already gifted members of the cast. And she, of course, is constantly making sure you can't look away from them in the show. With this Lora, her base outfit is defined and the swimsuit one is supported, though not perfect. And, of course, an ability to put her in different outfits.

How to use it:

(I use Sampling Method DPM++ SDE Karras and Upscaler R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B).

0.7 to 1 depending on model/lora/etc combination.

Main Triggers

LucoaDM, CasualCL, wearing CasualCL, shorts, tank top, thighhighs - For the base outfit that she wears

LucoaDM, SwimCL, wearing SwimCL - For her swimsuit outfit on the show. This one doesn't work perfectly every time but I figured I should keep it as an option.

Other Stuff

Anything else you want to describe the outfit and more!

Extra, Extra!: Should be well trained and usable in most models. Images shown for example.

Picture Descriptions:

1-2: AnythingV3 with just this Lora's base outfit.

2: AnythingV3 with just this Lora's swimsuit outfit.

4: AbyssOrange with just this Lora.

5: RevAnimated with just this Lora.

How was it trained?

It was trained on animefull_final with 31 images with the usual self-pruning and tagging and a wide range of different images. I like keeping my prompts simple for the first few pictures so that you can see it without a whole bunch of mumbo jumbo. Make your pictures better than mine though!

items.name: BananaCatMix
items.description:
声明：模型禁止任何形式的转载和二次发布，供学习参考经验交流，可自由融模，不得用于商用或其他非法用途。

The cover cat girl is Lily Meow, and everyone passing by can SQUISH THAT CAT and give her a thumbs up :3

  • 中文简介：

（我愿称之为模型大杂烩，边用边融的产物，不小心出了个相对还不错的融模。）

模型基底已经无从考究，我目前能记得的有Cetus、Orange、AnythingV5、PVC、Lyriel、LigneClaire等可能还有更多，权重数值几乎是脑内配比，少量测试，所以自认为这是依托答辩，但还挺好用的。

该模型是一个偏向二次元画风的融模，能稳定的输出细节较多的二次元画风人物，整体画风如示意图所示，喜爱的朋友可以按需取用。

依托于融了很多千奇百怪的模型，这个融模对tag的识别度还是相当好的，基本不是很怪的词都可以识别并在画面里体现，可以很轻松的达到你想要的效果，还有很多奇妙画风模型，关键词打对的时候还会有惊喜。并且，因为融了不少3D设计以及风景等现实模型，所以生成纯风景/物品相关图片时也能达到很精美的效果。

推荐参数：

正面tag推荐用masterpiece, best quality起手，反面常用low quality, worst quality等都可，可以参考例图的负面，屎山负面大欢迎，EasyNegative大欢迎。

CFG我一般用默认7，往上往下走其实也都可以，大家可以试试有没有其妙效果。

采样器测下来其实都挺适合的，各有所长吧，自用最多是Euler（出图快）、Euler a（出图快）、DPM++ 2M SDE Karras（质量好）、DDIM（手崩的少）。

不用高清修复出图还可以，如果人物或者物体太小的话细节会崩，建议用下高修，个人目前一般常用Latent (bicubic antialiased)、R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B，前者能出更多小细节但容易瞎长，后者比较好稳定高修之前的图片特征。

v3b内置了一个840000的VAE，色彩比较浓厚，喜欢清淡的可以自行调整至其他。v3e2忘记放VAE了，使用时需要手动添加一下，推荐ClearVAE。

  • English Introduction：

(I would like to call it a hodgepodge of models, the product of merge while using, and accidentally producing a relatively good merged model.)

The model base is no longer available, I can currently remember Cetus, Orange, AnythingV5, PVC, Lyriel, LigneClaire, etc. There may be more, the weight value is almost from my mind, a small number of tests, so I would call it a piece of ****, but it is quite useful.

The model is a merged model biased towards the ACG painting style, which can stably output the ACG painting style characters with more details, and the overall painting style is shown in the pictures, and you guys can take it as needed.

Relying on a lot of amazing models, this model is still quite good at the recognition of prompts, basically not very strange words can be recognized and reflected in the picture, can easily achieve the effect you want, there are many wonderful styles, will be surprises when the keywords are right. In addition, because many 3D designs and realistic models such as landscapes are merged in, it is possible to achieve beautiful results when generating pure landscape/object-related images.

Recommended parameters:

The positive prompts recommends using "masterpiece, best quality" to start, negative commonly used "low quality, worst quality," etc., or you can use negative prompts from sample images, and EasyNegative is welcome.

CFG I generally use the default 7, up and down can actually be good, you can try to see if there is a wonderful effect.

All the samplers are actually quite suitable, each has its own strengths, self-use is Euler (fast drawing), Euler a (fast drawing), DPM++ 2M SDE Karras (good quality), DDIM (less hand collapse).

If the character or object is too small, the details will collapse, it is recommended to use the Hires.Fix, personally generally used Latent (bicubic antialiased), R-ESRGAN 4x + Anime6B, the former can produce more small details, the latter is better to stabilize the picture characteristics before the Hires.Fix.

v3b version Built-in an 840000 VAE, the color is relatively strong, if you like light, you can adjust to others. And I forgot to add VAE in v3e2, need to set VAE manually when using, recommend ClearVAE.

items.name: Made Of Iridescent Foil
items.description:
Iridescent foil refers to a type of metallic foil that displays a captivating and shifting range of colors when it catches and reflects light.

This special foil is designed to create a shimmering effect, similar to the changing colors seen on the surface of a soap bubble or the scales of certain fish. It is commonly used in various creative applications, including packaging, printing, stationery, crafts, and decorative arts.

Iridescent foil is made by combining layers of thin, translucent materials that reflect and refract light differently. As light hits the surface of the foil, it undergoes interference and diffraction, resulting in a display of vibrant, rainbow-like colors that shift and change as the viewing angle or lighting conditions vary.

The colors produced by iridescent foil can range from subtle pastel hues to vibrant and intense shades, depending on the specific materials and manufacturing processes used. This makes it a popular choice for adding a touch of visual interest, elegance, and a hint of magic to various projects.

The unique and eye-catching qualities of iridescent foil make it a versatile material for enhancing designs and adding a touch of whimsy. Whether it's used to accentuate text, create patterns, or as a decorative element, iridescent foil offers a captivating and ethereal aesthetic that can elevate the visual appeal of any project.
